@zwass unfortunately no, you can't say "this needs to be changed and approved in order to be committed". The way this is usually solved in practice is only project owners can push to a repo, so only they can merge "approved" PRs.

Generally, a "lgtm" or something is needed before merging.

Also, I don't think you can comment on multiple lines on a PR. It auto-adds the above 10 or so lines, so I would just comment on the last line that you'd want to comment on.

